column5: Yesterday I checked the forecast and saw that it was going to be –6 feels like –12 this morning and thought, forget it.  The water I wanted to fish was still high and stained and I thought, no way.  Seems Highdrifters (Fidel) enthusiasm is infectious because today at 7am I somehow found myself beside a river. Not the one I was hoping to fish but a river nonetheless. Glad I did!  We both ended the day 3/4 and getting into some nice fish…             Thanks for Reading.
Good Job Laz....what is the red spot on the last fish behind the eye?  just some kindof marking?
Fidel's lipstick probably rubbed off on the poor thing.
what's up with te last pic...is that a huge cut in the fish?or is it a leaf?
Great report Laz...Well done to the both of you.  Beauty fish all-around.  Battling the wind and cold definitely paid off
The fish had a huge cut on the top of it's head.
Excellent pictures.Love the shot in the water.
Nice goin' boys! (That's a pretty funky looking red patch on that one fishes head. Strange.)
Bahahah..  Yeah wut's up with that red dot??  Does it change colour when she gets mad or something??!!

And for the love of Peter let's sleep in next time brah!!  We're at the rivah at 6:15am and we have to wait until after 10 for our first fish??  That's just ridonculous!  Good times mang, good times.  HD
